<!DOCTYPE html>
<html id="toolkit-components" lang="en-us" dir="ltr">
    {{> tags/head secondaryCSS='toolkit'}}
    <body itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/WebPage">

        <div class="wrapper">

            {{>toolkit/accessibility-skip-to-element-1 id='skip-to-content' url='#main' title='skip to content'}}

            <header>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="small-12 columns">
                        <a href="{{www}}toolkit">Toolkit</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </header>

            <nav>
                <div class="row collapse">
                    <ul class="small-12 columns">
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit">Home</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/grid.html">Grid</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/panels.html">Panels</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/colors.html">Colors</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/text.html">Text</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/sprite.html">Sprite</a></li>
                        <li><a href="{{www}}toolkit/elements.html">Elements</a></li>
                        <li><a class="selected" href="{{www}}toolkit/components.html">Components</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </nav>

            <main id="main" tabindex="-1">
                <section>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="small-12 columns">
                            <h1>Components</h1>

                            <h2>Forms</h2>
                            <p>script: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/form-1.js">form-1.js</a></p>
                            <h3>form-1</h3>

                            <form class="form-1" id="form-1-example" name="form-1-example">

                                <fieldset class="fieldset-1">

                                    <legend class="legend-1">Tell us about your vehicle</legend>

                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='What is the make of the vehicle?' for='input-text-1-example'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/input-text-1 id='input-text-1-example' name='input-text-1-example' placeholder='i.e. Buick' type='text' required=true}}</p>

                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='what type of vehicle is it?' for='select-1-example'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/select-1 select-1 id='select-1-example' name='select-1-example' required=true}}</p>

                                    <p id="radio-group-label">Do you own or lease the vehicle?</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='own' for='input-radio-1-example-1'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/input-radio-1 id='input-radio-1-example-1' name='radio-example' labelledby='radio-group-label'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='lease' for='input-radio-1-example-2'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/input-radio-1 id='input-radio-1-example-2' name='radio-example' labelledby='radio-group-label'}}</p>

                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='please provide any additonal comments:' for='textarea-1-example'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/textarea-1 id='textarea-1-example' name='textarea-1-example' placeholder='please be detailed' required=true}}</p>

                                </fieldset>

                                <fieldset class="fieldset-1">

                                    <legend class="legend-1">Agree to terms</legend>

                                    <p>{{> toolkit/label-1 title='I agree to terms and conditions.' for='input-checkbox-1-example'}}</p>
                                    <p>{{> toolkit/input-checkbox-1 id='input-checkbox-1-example' name='checkbox-example' checked=true required=true}}</p>

                                </fieldset>

                                <p>{{> toolkit/button-1 id='button-1' type='submit' title='save your changes'}}</p>

                            </form>
                            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                            <h4>Gherkin</h4>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I submit a form with validation errors<br>
                                THEN I will be focused on the first form field in error state<br>
                                THEN I will hear the label for that form field<br>
                                THEN I will hear if the form field is required<br>
                                THEN I will hear a description of how to fix the error.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <hr>

                            <h2>Modals</h2>
                            <p>style: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/style/base/_components.scss">_components.scss</a></p>
                            <p>script: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/modal-open-1.js">modal-open-1.js</a>, <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/modal-1.js">modal-1.js</a></p>
                            <h3>modal-1</h3>
                            <p><button class="button-1" data-modal-open="modal-example-1">view disclosures</button></p>
                            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                            <h4>Gherkin</h4>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I activate a button to call a dialog (the control is NOT a link)<br>
                                THEN the keyboard focus goes to the active dialog<br>
                                AND I hear the screen reader read the title of the dialog<br>
                                (AND the button in default focus, if applicable)<br>
                                AND I cannot escape the dialog with the tab key<br>
                                AND I can escape the dialog with the escape key<br>
                                AND WHEN I close the dialog, the focus goes back to the original button<br>
                                (OR to the most appropriate place, if the button is not appropriate)</p>
                            </div>

                            <hr>

                            <h2>Tab Panels</h2>
                            <p>style: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/style/base/_components.scss">_components.scss</a></p>
                            <p>script: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/tabpanel-1.js">tabpanel-1.js</a></p>
                            <h3>tabpanel-1</h3>
                            <div class="tabpanel-1">
                                <ul role="tablist">
                                    <li id="tab-1" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-1" aria-selected="true" tabindex="0">dashboard</a></li>
                                    <li id="tab-2" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-2" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">account</a></li>
                                    <li id="tab-3" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-3" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">services</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                <div id="panel-1" aria-labelledby="tab-1" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="false">
                                    <p>dashboard landing content</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="panel-2" aria-labelledby="tab-2" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <p>account content</p>
                                </div>
                                <div id="panel-3" aria-labelledby="tab-3" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="true">
                                    <p>services content</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3>tabpanel-2</h3>
                            <div class="tabpanel-2">
                                <div role="tablist">
                                    <a id="tab-4" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-4" aria-selected="true" tabindex="0">dashboard</a>
                                    <div id="panel-4" aria-labelledby="tab-4" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="false">
                                        <p>dashboard landing content</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <a id="tab-5" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-5" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">account</a>
                                    <div id="panel-5" aria-labelledby="tab-5" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="true">
                                        <p>account content</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <a id="tab-6" role="tab" aria-controls="panel-6" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">services</a>
                                    <div id="panel-6" aria-labelledby="tab-6" role="tabpanel" aria-hidden="true">
                                        <p>services content</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                            <h4>Gherkin</h4>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I navigate to a tabpanel widget with the tab key, the focus should land on the active tab.<br>
                                WHEN I hit tab again, the focus should go past the remaining tabs to the next focusable item (beyond the tablist).<br>
                                IF I need to navigate within the tabs, when the keyboard focus is on the active tab, I can use the right arrow key to go forward through the tabs, or the left arrow key to go backward through tabs.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I land on the active tab using the tab key, the screen reader reads the label for the tab, it says "tab," it says how many tabs are in the group,<br>
                                AND which tab it is (e.g. "tab 1 of 4")<br>
                                AND it says "selected." When I navigate with the arrow keys to other tabs, it says all of the above plus gives the accurate location (e.g. "tab 2 of 4").</p>
                            </div>

                            <hr>

                            <h2>Accessible Ajax</h2>
                            <p>script: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/accessiblity-ajax-1.js">accessiblity-ajax-1.js</a>, <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/accessiblity-speaker-1.js">accessiblity-speaker-1.js</a></p>
                            <h3>accessiblity-ajax-1</h3>
                            <button id="accessible-ajax-example-button" class="button-1">click to load asynchronous content</button>
                            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                            <h4>Gherkin</h4>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I click a button with that executes an ajax request<br>
                                THEN IF the request response is slow I will hear that content is loading before the request is complete<br>
                                THEN I will hear a message that content has been loaded after the request is complete<br>
                                AND I will see focus visual change<br>
                                AND I will hear the new content added to the page</p>
                            </div>

                            <hr>

                            <h2>Videos</h2>
                            <p>script: <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/youtube-api-1.js">youtube-api-1.js</a>, <a href="{{webRepo}}app/assets/script/view/toolkit/youtube-player-1.js">youtube-player-1.js</a></p>
                            <h3>youtube-1</h3>
                            {{> toolkit/youtube-player-1 widescreen=true}}
                            <h3>Accessibility</h3>
                            <h4>Gherkin</h4>
                            <div class="gherkin">
                                <p>GIVEN I am a screen reader user<br>
                                WHEN I navigate to the iframe with my keyboard<br>
                                THEN I will hear 'YouTube video player'<br>
                                AND I will be able to navigate the iframe content</p>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </main>

            {{>toolkit/footer-1}}

        </div>

        {{> config/config}}
        {{> tags/script script='assets/script/global.compiled.js'}}

    </body>
</html>
